  m_Name: Quiz_L1060_06
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  question: Why do we attach the script to the parent object instead of the child?
  optionList:
  - The child can't run scripts
  - To keep the logic and visuals separated
  - Because the child is not a GameObject
  - It automatically boosts performance
  correctOptionIndex: 1
  answer: Keeping logic and visuals separate helps keep things clean and easy to
    manage. The parent holds the logic (script, physics), while the child handles
    visuals (sprite, VFX).
